'''Aunt Liddy''' is one of [[Ross Geller|Ross]] and [[Monica Geller]]'s aunts.

In "[[The One Where No One Proposes]]", when [[Jack Geller]] comes to see [[Emma Geller-Greene|Emma]] after her birth, Ross asks him where [[Judy Geller|Judy]] is. He says that she is picking up Aunt Liddy. This excites Monica because it means that she and Ross get "five dollars each!" Aunt Liddy, however, is not seen in the episode.

It is unknown if Aunt Liddy is from [[Jack Geller|Jack]]'s or [[Judy Geller|Judy]]'s part of the family, and whether she is a sister or a cousin of one of the Gellers.
